"I kept thinking =E2=80=94 what if my family couldn't get out of the car?"

By *Sarah M.*, CAA Member since 2016  =C2=B7  3 min read

"Hi, my name is Sarah. I'm a mom of two from Mississauga, and I want to
share something that changed the way I think about every car ride I take
with my kids."

Last winter, I watched a news story about a family whose car slid off the
road into a ditch. The doors were jammed. The seatbelts locked. They were
trapped for over 20 minutes in -18=C2=B0C weather before help arrived.

That night I couldn't sleep. I kept thinking =E2=80=94 *what if that was us=
? What
if I couldn't get my kids out?*

I called CAA the next morning. They pointed me to something I had never
heard of =E2=80=94 a *2-in-1 Car Window Breaker and Seatbelt Cutter*. Small=
 enough
to fit in your palm. Strong enough to save your family's life.

